## Quick Start

```
1. rebrew todo --json                          # get highest ROI action items
2. rebrew skeleton 0x<VA>                      # generate .c skeleton
3. rebrew test src/{target_name}/<func>.c --json  # compile + compare
4. # iterate code until STATUS: EXACT or RELOC
5. rebrew test --all --json                    # batch promote all ready functions
```

## CLI Tools

Use `--json` for structured output (preferred for agents).

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `rebrew todo --json` | Prioritized action items (compile errors, near misses, new functions) |
| `rebrew skeleton 0x<VA>` | Generate C skeleton from address |
| `rebrew test <file> --json` | Compile and byte-compare against target |
| `rebrew test --all --json` | Batch test all reversed functions |
| `rebrew diff <file> --json` | Structured byte diff vs target |
| `rebrew match <file> --json` | Run GA matching engine |
| `rebrew ga --near-miss --threshold 5` | Batch GA on MATCHING functions with small deltas |
| `rebrew ga --json` | Batch GA on all STUB functions |
| `rebrew rename <old> <new>` | Rename function and update cross-references |
| `rebrew verify --json` | Bulk verify all reversed files |
| `rebrew lint --json` | Validate annotations |
| `rebrew data --json` | Inventory globals in .data/.rdata/.bss |
| `rebrew graph --format summary` | Dependency graph stats and blockers |
| `rebrew catalog --json` | Generate coverage catalog |
| `rebrew flirt --json` | FLIRT scan for known library functions |
| `rebrew extract --json` | Batch extract and disassemble functions |
| `rebrew asm 0x<VA> --size 128 --json` | Quick offline disassembly |
| `rebrew sync --push` | Push annotations to Ghidra |
| `rebrew sync --summary --json` | Preview what would be synced |

## Annotation Format

Every reversed `.c` file starts with a **stable identity header** — only the
information that is intrinsic to the function and never changes:

```c
// FUNCTION: {target_name} 0x<virtual_address>
// SYMBOL: _function_name                 ← optional, derived from C definition

void __cdecl function_name(void)
{{
    // stub
}}
```

Volatile metadata (status, size, compiler flags, notes, blockers) is stored
**outside** the `.c` file in a per-directory `rebrew-functions.toml` sidecar file:

```toml
[0x10001234]
status = "STUB"
size   = 42
cflags = "/O2 /Gd"
blocker = "register allocation"
note   = "inline asm detected"
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never manually edit `rebrew-functions.toml`.** It is managed exclusively by Rebrew
> CLI tools (`rebrew test`, `rebrew match`, `rebrew diff --fix-blocker`, etc.).  Manual
> edits will be lost or corrupt the file and break tool workflows.

**STATUS values**: `EXACT` (byte-perfect) > `RELOC` (match after masking
relocations) > `MATCHING` (close) > `STUB` (incomplete)

`CFLAGS` is optional — falls back to the target default from `rebrew-project.toml`.

